<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1146,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1146,1172]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished from other congeners by the following combination of characters: wings hyaline, thorax with disrupted stripe of dense silvery gray microtomentum laterad of dorsocentral line; tergites 
<number box="[244,259,1226,1252]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[315,330,1226,1252]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
with dense silvery gray microtomentose spots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1146,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,1266,1292]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description.</emphasis>
Adults, small shore flies, body length 
<quantity box="[803,910,1266,1292]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.91">0.91 mm</quantity>
; yellowish brown to brown with silvery gray and yellowish silver microtomentum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1146,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis box="[198,262,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Head</emphasis>
. Frons yellowish brown with yellowish silver microtomentum slightly darker than anterior semicircle, ocellar circle darker, same color as frons. Occiput with broad band of silvery gray microtomentum extending ventrally from medial vertical seta and contiguous with the thoracic vitta, mediolaterally dark brown, bare along posterior eye margin. Lateral vertical setae broken. Scape brown; basal flagellomere and arista of single specimen missing. Facial background yellowish brown with silvery gray microtomentum; band of silvery gray microtomentum along eye margin from the lateral vertical seta, along parafacial, and extending to the gena. Gena covered with silvery gray microtomentum; postgena ventrally shiny, brown. Maxillary palpus yellow; prementum yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1146,2012]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,152,858]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis box="[198,283,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Thorax</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[309,399,1666,1692]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 17" captionStartId="11.[151,269,1620,1644]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,194,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,194,1596]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 17. Dorsal view of microtomentose patterns on mesonotum: 15. Nostima duoseta Cresson (male). 16. N. kiwistriata sp. nov. (female). 17. N. negramaculata sp. nov. (male). Scale bar = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/179961/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[366,399,1666,1692]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutal length 
<quantity box="[587,697,1666,1692]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.50 mm</quantity>
; scutellar length 
<quantity box="[903,1013,1666,1692]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.22">0.22 mm</quantity>
. Mesonotum yellowish-brown with yellowish silver microtomentum, with darker vittae medially and along dorsocentral line; silvery gray microtomentose vitta lateral to dorsocentral line, broken at point above notopleuron, anteriorly vitta covering postpronotum; scutellum yellowish-brown with yellowish silver microtomentum slightly darker laterally as along dorsocentral line, laterally with dense silvery gray microtomentum contiguous with silvery gray lateral vitta on mesonotum; anepisternum yellowish brown with yellowish silver microtomentum; katepisternum yellowish brown with yellowish silver microtomentum; anatergite yellowish brown with yellowish silver microtomentum. Chaetotaxy: anterior dorsocentral seta 
<number box="[746,761,1946,1972]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[771,784,1946,1972]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
length of posterior seta; notopleural setae of single specimen missing; lateral scutellar seta 
<number box="[618,629,1986,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[641,656,1986,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
length of apical seta. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[997,1085,1986,2012]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 21" captionStartId="12.[151,269,1271,1295]" captionTargetBox="[150,1422,611,1237]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[147,1441,594,1247]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 21. Right wing, dorsal view: 18. Nostima duoseta Cresson (male). 19. N. kiwistriata sp. nov. (female). 20. N. negramaculata sp. nov. (male). 21. N. negramaculata sp. nov. (male). Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/179962/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1052,1085,1986,2012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
): length 
<quantity box="[1188,1297,1986,2012]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.46" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="1.46">1.46 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="0.53">0.53 mm</quantity>
; costal-vein ratio 
<number box="[407,462,152,178]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="0.82">0.82</number>
; M-vein ration 
<number box="[642,697,152,178]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="0.2">0.20</number>
; amber background with pale brown veins and crossveins. Halter yellowish white. Legs yellowish brown; metathoracic tibia with darker brown bands; tarsomere 
<number box="[1310,1325,192,218]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
dark yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,858]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis box="[198,309,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[325,438,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 8" captionStartId="8.[151,269,1490,1514]" captionTargetBox="[617,965,919,1461]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[607,974,908,1468]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 8. Nostima kiwistriata sp. nov. (female). 7. Abdominal tergites, microtomentose patterns, dorsal view. 8. Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/179959/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Figs. 
<number box="[390,438,272,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Background brown; tergites 
<number box="[791,806,272,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[861,876,272,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
medially with sparse, silvery gray microtomentum; tergite 
<number box="[304,319,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="3.0">3</number>
medially with dense silvery microtomentum and posterolaterally with small silver-colored microtomentose circular spots; tergite 
<number box="[610,625,352,378]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="4.0">4</number>
shiny, bare with dense, silvery gray spots posterolaterally; tergite 
<number box="[1422,1437,352,378]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
shiny, bare.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,858]" box="[198,633,432,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis box="[198,388,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Male terminalia</emphasis>
